<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>Colors</title>
    </head>
    <body>

        <p>Same as color name "Tomato":</p>

        <!-- Tomato color examples using different color value formats -->

        <h1 style="background-color:rgb(255, 99, 71); border: 10px solid purple; color:black;">rgb(255, 99, 71)</h1>
        <h1 style="background-color:#ff6347; border: 2px dotted blue; color:black;">#ff6347</h1>
        <h1 style="background-color:hsl(9, 100%, 64%); color: black;">hsl(9, 100%, 64%)</h1>

        <p>Same as color name "Tomato", but 50% transparent:</p>
        <h1 style="background-color:rgba(255, 99, 71, 0.5);">rgba(255, 99, 71, 0.5)</h1>
        <h1 style="background-color:hsla(9, 100%, 64%, 0.5);">hsla(9, 100%, 64%, 0.5)</h1>

        <p>In addition to the predefined color names, colors can be specified using RGB, HEX, HSL, or even transparent colors using RGBA or HSLA color values.</p>

    </body>
</html>

